                        <div class="cognitive-text">
                           <h2>Gain insights into your APIs</h2>
                            <p>Get a better understanding of how your APIs are performing and being used. Get near real-time analytics reports and identify trends that might affect your business. You can also log request and response data for further online and offline analysis.</p>
                        </div>
                    </li>
                </ul>
                <img src="//resource.cdn.azure.cn/marketing-resource/css/images/api-management-diagram-cn.png" alt=""/>   
                <h2>Provide a first-rate developer experience</h2> 
                <ul>
                    <li>Self-service API key management</li>
                    <li>Auto-generated API catalog, documentation, and code samples</li>
                    <li>OAuth-enabled API console for browsing APIs without writing a line of code</li>
                    <li>Sign in using popular Internet identity providers and Azure Active Directory</li>
                </ul>
                <h2>Protect and optimize your APIs</h2> 
                <ul>
                    <li>Use transformation policies to simplify and optimize requests and responses</li>
                    <li>Use keys, JSON Web Token (JWT) validation and IP filtering to protect APIs</li>
                    <li>Use quotas and rate limits to protect your APIs from overload and overuse</li>
                    <li>Use response caching to improve latency and perform scaling</li>
                </ul>
                <h2>Manage all your APIs in one place</h2> 
                <ul>
                    <li>Expose all APIs behind a single static IP and domain</li>
                    <li>Get near real-time usage, performance, and health status analytics</li>
                    <li>Automate management and integration using REST API, PowerShell, and Git</li>
                    <li>Set up API Management and scale it in one or more geographical regions</li>
                </ul>
                <h2>Connect to back-end services anywhere</h2> 
                <ul>
                    <li>Client certificate authentication</li>
                    <li>Azure virtual networks</li>
                    <li>Azure ExpressRoute</li>
                </ul>
